    • stateDeterminer

      public int[] stateDeterminer(int handValue, boolean containsAce)
      Determines and packages HashMap identifiers for linearOperator querying.

      Booleans are parsed as integers and then packaged in array with handValue as args for queryLinOps method.

      Parameters:
      handValue - the value of the current hand.
      containsAce - whether the current hand contains an ace.
      Returns:
      an array converting game states into integers to be parsed by the query method.

    • queryLinOps

      Returns:
      Linear operator array corresponding to inputs.

    • getFrequencyList

      public ArrayList<Integer> getFrequencyList(Hand hand)
      Fetches frequency list of counted card for given hand.

      Calls method from BlackJack class for determining cards visible to hand. Once cards are counted, list is parsed to determine frequency of each card which is then passed into ArrayList.

      Parameters:
      hand - hand to determine visible card list from.
      Returns:
      ArrayList of counted card frequencies.

    • frequencyAdjuster

      public ArrayList<Double> frequencyAdjuster(ArrayList<Integer> inList, int deckCount)
      Takes frequency list and deckCount then adjusts frequencies to correspond to deckCount.

      Divides frequencies by amount of decks to make more similar frequencies across multideck games. Converts integers to doubles then divides by deckCount.

      Parameters:
      inList - frequency list to divide and adjust.
      deckCount - number of decks to divide by.
      Returns:
      outList equal to frequencies divided by deckCount.

    • mlChoice

      public boolean mlChoice(Hand handParam, int deckCount)
      Gets frequency list, deck count, and hand before passing to getChoice function.

      Gets frequency list for hand, then passes to frequency adjuster along with deckCount, then passes adjusted frequency list to getChoice.

      Parameters:
      handParam - hand to calculate frequency from and to determine choice for.
      deckCount - amount of decks to adjust frequency by.
      Returns:
      boolean of whether to hit or not depending on machine learning algorithm.

    • getChoice

      public boolean getChoice(Hand handParam, ArrayList<Double> frequencyListParam)
      Handles hand values and frequency list to determine the best choice for AI dependent on linear operators.

      Determines current hand value first, if 10 or less true, if 21 or greater false, in case hand value between 10 and 21, further state data is determined and stateDeterminer called. Corresponding Linear Operator Bra is called and frequencyList Ket is multiplied <linOpp| * |frequencyList> to obtain the betModifier. If the resulting betModifier is negative will not hit, otherwise will hit.

      Parameters:
      handParam - hand to determine best play for.
      frequencyListParam - frequency ket to use in algorithm.
      Returns:
      decision based on betModifier.
